# Image Composition Rule

**Never** default to a plain rectangular `<img>` element sitting inside a card or list row.

## Patterns to use

### Cinematic hero header (category/section headers with background images)
```tsx
<div className="relative h-32 overflow-hidden bg-[#0d1117]">
  <img src={url} alt="" aria-hidden className="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-center opacity-20" />
  <div className="hero-overlay-h" />  {/* horizontal gradient: dark-left → transparent-right */}
  <div className="hero-overlay-v" />  {/* vertical vignette: dark-bottom → transparent-top */}
  <div className="absolute inset-0 flex items-end px-5 pb-4 gap-3">
    {/* content here */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Edge-bleed row item (replaces boxed thumbnails in list rows)
Row container must have `relative overflow-hidden`. Remove the `<img>` and replace with:
```tsx
{imageUrl && (
  <div
    className="absolute left-0 top-0 w-32 h-full opacity-20 pointer-events-none"
    style={{
      backgroundImage: `url(${imageUrl})`,
      backgroundSize: "cover",
      backgroundPosition: "center",
      maskImage: "linear-gradient(to right, transparent, black 50%, transparent)",
      WebkitMaskImage: "linear-gradient(to right, transparent, black 50%, transparent)",
    }}
  />
)}
```

### Full-bleed card background (upgrade ads, feature cards)
```tsx
<div className="relative rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-[#0a0d14]">
  {imageUrl && (
    <>
      <div
        className="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.12] pointer-events-none"
        style={{ backgroundImage: `url(${imageUrl})`, backgroundSize: "cover", backgroundPosition: "center right" }}
      />
      <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#0a0d14] via-[#0a0d14]/80 to-transparent pointer-events-none" />
    </>
  )}
  <div className="relative p-4">{/* content */}</div>
</div>
```

### Small icon polish (w-7 to w-12 thumbnails that must remain inline)
Replace `border border-[#1f2937]` with `ring-1 ring-white/10 shadow-md` and increase border-radius to `rounded-xl`:
```tsx
<img src={url} alt={name} className="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl object-cover ring-1 ring-white/10 shadow-md shrink-0" />
```

## Rules
- Images should feel **embedded** into the section, not framed
- Use `aria-hidden` and empty `alt=""` on purely decorative/background images
- Prefer `opacity-20` to `opacity-50` for background layers — subtlety is cinematic
- Always pair a background image with a gradient overlay so text remains readable
- QR codes (`data:image/svg+xml`) are functional — leave them as plain `<img>`
- Mascot images in `OmniMascot.tsx` use their own system — do not apply these patterns there
